CONTAGIOUS BOVINE PLEUROPNEUMONIA - NIGERIA
*******************************************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: 25 Oct 1999
From: Tam Garland <tgarland@cvm.tamu.edu>
Source: OIE Reporting

Suspicion
Emergency report
Text of a fax received on 20 October 1999 from Dr Ja'afaru Ladan, Director
of the Department of Livestock and Pest Control Services, Federal Ministry
of Agriculture, Water Resources and Rural Development, Abuja:
Report date: 14 September 1999.
An outbreak of contagious bovine pleuropneumonia in three herds of trade
cattle moving from Gumel (12ยบ 38' N * 9ยบ 21' E) in Jigawa State, to Wake
(9ยบ 52 N * 8ยบ E) in Kaduna State, took place between 15 July and 16 August
1999.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species: bov
susceptible: 1,191
cases: 340
deaths 41
destroyed: ----
slaughtered:---
Diagnosis: lung samples have been forwarded to the National Veterinary
Research Institute, Vom, for confirmation of the disease.
Control measures during reporting period: the animals have been quarantined
and ring vaccination has been conducted in the area.
--
